==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thrall
<hw>Thrall</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>thral</ets>,
<ets>⟦thorn⟧ral</ets>, Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧r⟦ae⟧ll</ets>, perhaps through
AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧r⟦aemac⟧l</ets>; akin to Sw. <ets>tr⟦aum⟧l</ets>, Dan.
<ets>tr⟦ae⟧l</ets>, and probably to AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧r⟦ae⟧gian</ets> to
run, Goth. <ets>⟦thorn⟧ragjan</ets>, Gr. <grk>tre`chein</grk>; cf. OHG.
<ets>dregil</ets>, <ets>drigil</ets>, a servant.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A slave; a bondman.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gurth, the born <qex>thrall</qex> of Cedric.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Slavery; bondage; servitude; thraldom.</def>
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He still in <qex>thrall</qex>⟦br⟧
Of all-subdoing sleep.</q> <rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A shelf; a stand for barrels, etc.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrall</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thrall
<hw>Thrall</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to a thrall; in the
condition of a thrall; bond; enslaved.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fiend that would make you <qex>thrall</qex> and bond.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrall</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Thrall
<hw>Thrall</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To enslave.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Poetic]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thralldom</ent>⟦br⟧
